               <persName xml:lang="it" xml:id="n1">Giovanni Battista Brocchi da Imola</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="la" xml:id="n2">Johannes Baptista Brocchus</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="en" xml:id="n3">Baptista of Imola</persName>
               <occupation type="political">Diplomat</occupation>
               <floruit notBefore="1480" notAfter="1493">
                  One or two persons named ‘(Johannes) Baptista of Imola’ were active in the period of c. 1480–1493. It is disputed whether the 
                  Giovanni Battista Brocchi da Imola, a nobleman and diplomat who accompanied an Ethiopian delegation from <placeName ref="LOC3957Jerusa">Jerusalem</placeName>
                  to <placeName ref="LOC5374Rome">Rome</placeName> in <date>1481–1482</date>, and the Baptista of Imola, 
                  a messenger who carried letters between <placeName ref="LOC3957Jerusa">Jerusalem</placeName> and 
                  <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName> in the period 1480–1484, are the same or two different persons (this view is argued for in
                  Krebs 2021, 136–139). 
               </floruit>
            </person>
